article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — AJ McKee scored 25 points as Queens beat Kennesaw State 91-82 on Friday night. McKee had six assists for the Royals (13-18, 7-9 Atlantic Sun Conference). Chris Ashby was 6 of 10 shooting (6 for 9 from 3-point range) to add 20 points. Deyton Albury shot 6 for 14 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 1 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 14 points. Jamel King led the way for the Owls (15-15, 6-10) with 21 points and nine rebounds. Demond Robinson added 13 points and six rebounds for Kennesaw State. In addition, Simeon Cottle finished with 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
